---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import EmotionalWellbeingDashboard from '../../components/dashboards/emotional-wellbeing/EmotionalWellbeingDashboard';
---

<BaseLayout title="Emotional Well-being — Teddy Wright"
  description="Rate your emotional needs by priority and how met they currently are. Surface highest-leverage needs, domain gaps, and which sources (self / friends / romantic / activities / career / other) are over- or under-contributing.">
  <section class="max-w-[1080px] mx-auto px-6 md:px-8 pt-12 pb-24">
    <a href="/dashboards" class="font-mono text-[11px] uppercase text-muted hover:text-accent no-underline" style="letter-spacing: 0.08em">← all dashboards</a>

    <header class="mt-4 mb-8 max-w-[640px]">
      <h1 class="font-display font-semibold text-[40px] leading-none m-0 mb-3 text-ink"
          style="letter-spacing: -0.03em">Emotional Well-being</h1>
      <p class="font-serif text-[16px] text-ink-soft leading-[1.6] m-0 mb-3">
        Rate your emotional needs by priority and how met they currently are.
        The dashboard surfaces the highest-leverage needs to act on,
        domain-level gaps, and which sources (self, friends, romantic, activities, career, other)
        are over- or under-contributing relative to where you'd want them.
      </p>
      <p class="font-mono text-[11px] uppercase text-muted leading-[1.5] m-0"
         style="letter-spacing: 0.08em">
        data lives in your browser only · export csv to keep it · import to restore
      </p>
    </header>

    <EmotionalWellbeingDashboard client:only="react" />

    <div class="mt-12 pt-6 border-t border-rule-soft font-serif text-[14px] text-ink-soft leading-[1.65] max-w-[720px]">
      <h2 class="font-display font-semibold text-[18px] text-ink m-0 mb-3" style="letter-spacing: -0.01em">How to use it</h2>
      <ol class="m-0 pl-5">
        <li class="mb-1">Skim the seeded needs. Add your own with <span class="font-mono text-[12px]">+ Add need</span>; remove any that don't apply via the row's expanded panel.</li>
        <li class="mb-1">For each one that matters, set <span class="font-mono text-[12px]">priority</span> (1 = not relevant → 5 = core) and <span class="font-mono text-[12px]">currently met</span> (1 = not at all → 7 = fully).</li>
        <li class="mb-1">Optional, deeper: expand a row (<span class="font-mono text-[12px]">▸</span>) and set how much of that need <em>actually</em> comes from each source vs. how much you'd want it to. The numbers don't have to sum to anything — they're just allocations.</li>
        <li>Switch to <span class="font-mono text-[12px]">Insights</span> to see leverage rankings, domain rollups, source gaps, and distributions.</li>
      </ol>
      <p class="m-0 mt-4 text-muted text-[13px]">
        Leverage = priority × (8 − met). High-priority + low-met needs surface first.
        Source gap = ideal − actual, priority-weighted across all rated needs.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
